          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636378942620-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636378942620-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636378942620-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the onion has softened</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>softened onion</strong> to the bowl of <strong>'Nduja</strong></p><p>Keep the remaining softened onion in the pan but remove the pan from the heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636378946756-x200.jpg",
